chart_description: This chart shows the I/O pressure stall time for some processes responsible for Disk operations. It is a measure of how much time system is under pressure to complete I/O requests when the request queue exceeds specific thresholds.

dimension_descriptions.some 10: This dimension represents the 10 seconds time window for which I/O pressure stall time is measured.
dimension_descriptions.some 300: This dimension represents the 5 minutes time window for which I/O pressure stall time is measured.
dimension_descriptions.some 60: This dimension represents the 1 minute time window for which I/O pressure stall time is measured.
